{{About|the common law legal procedure}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}}
{{Refimprove|date=December 2008}}

An '''allocution''', or '''allocutus''', is a formal statement made to the court by the defendant who has been found [[guilt (law)|guilty]] prior to being sentenced. It is part of the criminal procedure in some jurisdictions using [[common law]].
